2 IMF Primary Commodity Prices

setwd("/Users/yamamoto/R/IMF")

vnames<-c("yearmonth",paste0("VAR",1:94,sep=""))

DB<-read_excel("external-dataJune2024.xlsx",skip=4,col_names = vnames)

DB$date= seq(as.Date("1990-01-01"),

2.1 砂糖 (1)

This is about `Sugar, Free Market, Coffee Sugar and Cocoa Exchange (CSCE) contract no.11 nearest future position, US cents per pound’

According to ICE, the Sugar No. 11 contract is the world benchmark contract for raw sugar trading. The contract prices the physical delivery of raw cane sugar, free-on-board the receiver’s vessel to a port within the country of origin of the sugar.

# First thing is to change your working directory
setwd("/users/yamamoto/R/IMF/")

# Sugar, Free Market, Coffee Sugar and Cocoa Exchange (CSCE) contract no.11 
# nearest future position, US cents per pound
# VAR62 (BK列)

# Dateクラスのベクトルを使って目盛位置を指定する。byで間隔の指定もできる。
datebreaksSG1 <- seq(as.Date("1999-01-01"), as.Date("2024-04-01"), 
                  by="18 month")



DB |>
  filter(date>"1999-01-01") |>
  ggplot()+
  geom_point(aes(x=date,y=VAR62),size=1)+
  geom_line(aes(x=date,y=VAR62))+
  xlab("month/year")+
  ylab("US cents per pound")+
  theme_bw()+
  labs(title="Sugar, Free Market, Coffee Sugar and Cocoa Exchange (CSCE)" ,
       subtitle="contract no.11, nearest future position",
       caption="Source: IMF Primary Commodity Price")+
  theme(plot.title    = element_text(size=14),
        plot.subtitle    = element_text(size=9),
    axis.title.x = element_text(size=12),
        axis.text.x = element_text(size=10,angle=30, hjust=1), 
      axis.title.y = element_text(size=12), 
      axis.text.y = element_text(size=12),
      legend.text = element_text(size=12),
      legend.title = element_text(size=12),
      plot.caption  = element_text(size=12)
      )+
  scale_x_date(breaks=datebreaksSG1,date_labels = "%b %y")+
  guides(size=none)->SG1

SG1

ggsave(filename = "SG2024april.pdf",plot=SG1,width=5, height=8,units="in")

2.3 比較

二つを同じグラフにプロットしてみる。

DB |>
  select(date,VAR62,VAR63) |>
  pivot_longer(c(VAR62,VAR63),names_to = "name") |>
  filter(date>"1999-01-01") |>
  ggplot()+
  geom_point(aes(x=date,y=value,color=name),size=1)+
  geom_line(aes(x=date,y=value,color=name))+
  xlab("month/year")+
  ylab("US cents per pound")+
  theme_bw()+
  labs(title="Sugar, Free Market (VAR62) and Sugar, U.S. import (VAR63)" ,
       subtitle="nearest futures position",
       caption="Source: IMF Primary Commodity Price")+
  theme(plot.title    = element_text(size=14),
        plot.subtitle    = element_text(size=9),
    axis.title.x = element_text(size=12),
        axis.text.x = element_text(size=10,angle=30, hjust=1), 
      axis.title.y = element_text(size=12), 
      axis.text.y = element_text(size=12),
      legend.text = element_text(size=12),
      legend.title = element_text(size=12),
      plot.caption  = element_text(size=12)
      )+
  scale_color_manual(values= met.brewer("Egypt", 2))+
  scale_x_date(breaks=datebreaksSG1,date_labels = "%b %y")+
  labs(color="")+
  guides(size=none)->SG2
